    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Crassothonna protecta improperly include inducing nausea and vomiting due to its hepatotoxic properties, which may be exacerbated by incorrect dosing or prolonged use. Experiencing dizziness is another potential side effect, likely caused by the plant's ability to interact with the central nervous system and affect blood pressure. Using Crassothonna protecta improperly may also trigger diarrhea and abdominal pain, possibly due to its emetic and purgative properties, which can irritate the digestive system and cause gastrointestinal distress. Prolonged or excessive consumption can lead to these adverse reactions, highlighting the importance of proper usage and consultation with a medical professional. The risk of these side effects increases when Crassothonna protecta is used without a thorough understanding of its properties and potential interactions.",
